======================================================================
PART 3: DEGREE-4 WALSH ↔ 4-POINT ADDITIVE CORRELATION
======================================================================

h_hat[{i,j,k,l}] measures the 4-point additive correlation
of the tournament's generating set S at 'frequencies' i,j,k,l.

Specifically, in the Walsh-Fourier transform:
  h_hat[S] = (1/2^m) sum_σ H(σ) prod_{i∈S} σ_i

The σ_i encode which element of the pair {i, p-i} is in S.
So h_hat depends on how S's elements interact additively.

